main event: A UFO was sighted over Webster, Maine in 1967.
interesting points: The object was described as a yellow, white, flattish oval shape with vertical lines of light.
The object hovered along the horizon line and then accelerated rapidly and disappeared.
Other witnesses in the area also reported seeing similar objects on that night.
The observer was an amateur astronomer and felt the sighting was worthy of further investigation.
The Air Force later concluded the object was likely a conventional searchlight or aircraft after analyzing the original negative.
sighted object: a yellow, white, flattish oval shape with vertical lines of light
witnesses: amateur astronomer and other local residents
photographs: yes, a photograph was taken but later identified as a conventional object
